SIMPLE: maslin
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maslin
<hw>Mas"lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>missellane</ets>, <ets>misceline</ets>, <ets>miscelin</ets>,
<ets>meslin</ets>, fr. <ets>miscellane</ets>. See
<er>Miscellane</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A mixture composed of
different materials</def>; especially: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A mixture of
metals resembling brass.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A mixture of different
sorts of grain, as wheat and rye.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>meslin</asp>, <asp>mislin</asp>, <asp>maselyn</asp>,
<asp>mastlin</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A vessel made of maslin, 1 <sd>(a)</sd>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mead eke in a <qex>maselyn</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maslin</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Maslin
<hw>Mas"lin</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Composed of different sorts;
<as>as, <ex>maslin</ex> bread, which is made of rye mixed with a little
wheat</as>.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>meslin</asp>,
<asp>mislin</asp>, etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mason</ent>⟦br⟧
